課程網址 Course Website: 

先修課程或先備能力 Prerequisite Course(s):   The main purpose of this course is to study and discuss pioneering and scholarly publications of enduring significance to urban, regional and national planning. To enhance this learning opportunity, experts may be invited to present their knowledge concerning important urban planning issues. Students will demonstrate their understanding of the presentations through submitted reports. Due to potential changes in speaker availability throughout the course of the semester and other unforeseeable circumstances, the schedule below should be considered flexible, and will be adjusted as necessary to accomplish the course objectives.       

